@startuml tiered-pr-review-flow
title Tiered PR Review: Flow and Gates

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam ActivityBackgroundColor #F5F5F5
skinparam ActivityBorderColor #666666
skinparam ActivityDiamondBackgroundColor #FFF3E0
skinparam ActivityDiamondBorderColor #666666

start
:PR opened or synchronized;

partition "Static CI (always runs, blocking)" {
  :pre-commit, actionlint + shellcheck self-test,
Bats and pytest suites, conventional-commit
title validation, CodeQL, secret scanning;
}

partition "Async AI Reviewers (always runs, non-blocking)" {
  :Copilot code review (auto-enrolled);
  :CodeRabbit comments on the diff;
}

if (Non-draft, same-repo PR targeting main?) then (yes)
  partition "Tier 0: claude-baseline-review.yml (advisory)" {
    :Classify PR into one of five classes:
renovate-deps, pattern-series, docs-only,
config-tweak, substantive;
    :Run the class-specific spot check;
    if (Deterministic escalation trigger fires?\n(workflow permissions/secrets/OIDC/triggers changed;\nscripts/ writes via gh api, secrets, transfer/delete;\nbreaking-change label or "!" in title;\n>500 changed lines excl. lockfiles/generated;\nrenovate tag/SHA mismatch or major bump;\nor reviewer judgment)) then (yes)
      :Verdict = ESCALATE;
      :Apply "needs-deep-review" label;
    else (no)
      :Verdict = BASELINE-OK;
    endif
    :Post ONE sticky comment\n(marker: claude-baseline-review)\nwith verdict, findings, and\nCopilot/CodeRabbit/CI status;
  }
else (no: draft, fork PR,\nor non-main target)
  :Tier 0 skipped;
  note right
    Fork PRs cannot read the API-key
    secret, so the job would only fail
    at startup there. Advisory only:
    a skipped or failed Tier 0 job
    never blocks other checks.
  end note
endif

if ("needs-deep-review" label applied?) then (yes)
  partition "Tier 1: /pr-review skill (manual, ByronWilliamsCPA/.claude)" {
    :Maintainer runs /pr-review;
    :Aggregate Copilot, CodeRabbit,\nSonarQube, and CI findings;
    :13 specialized agents + premise gate\n-> confidence-scored, deduplicated,\nconsensus-validated findings across\nfour severity tiers;
    :Maintainer runs /pr-fix to remediate;
  }
else (no)
  :PR remains gated only by the\nstatic layer plus raw bot comments\n(no deep pass);
endif

:Maintainer merge decision;
stop

note left
  **Source:**
  [[../tiered-pr-review.md]]

  Tier 0 is advisory only: its verdict is a
  sticky comment plus a label, never a merge
  block. Escalation is deterministic where
  possible (doc section 3); "reviewer
  judgment" is the catch-all sixth trigger.
  Docs-only changes, pattern-series PRs
  matching their precedent, and clean
  patch/minor pin bumps do not escalate
  on their own.
end note

@enduml
